urban%20poverty%2C%20according%20to%20new%20US%20Census%20data.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20people%20living%20in%20poverty%20in%20the%20US%20grew%20by%20about%201.5%20million%20to%20a%20total%20of%20almost%2041%20million%20between%202019%20and%202022%2C%20bringing%20the%20rate%20of%20poverty%20to%2012.6%25%20nationwide%2C%20up%20from%2012.3%25%20in%202019%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Census%20Bureau's%20most%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fprograms-surveys%2Facs%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Community%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20population%20living%20in%20poverty%20grew%20three%20times%20as%20fast%20in%20major%20metro%20suburbs%20as%20it%20did%20in%20major%20cities%20between%202019%20and%202022%2C%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%20found%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fpost-pandemic-poverty-is-rising-in-americas-suburbs%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%20More%20than%2060%25%20of%20the%20growth%20in%20poverty%20across%20the%20country%20occurred%20in%20the%20suburbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20plurality%20of%20Americans%20call%20the%20country's%20increasingly%20diverse%20suburbs%20home.%20Nearly%20half%20of%20people%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%2047%25%20%E2%80%94%20live%20in%20suburbs%2C%2021%25%20live%20in%20major%20cities%20with%20over%20500%2C000%20residents%2C%2018%25%20live%20in%20small%20and%20medium-sized%20metro%20areas%2C%20and%2014%25%20live%20in%20rural%20areas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuburban%20communities%20in%20major%20metro%20areas%20in%20the%20South%2C%20West%2C%20and%20Midwest%2C%20including%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20Houston%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20Ogden%2C%20Utah%2C%20St.%20Louis%2C%20and%20Minneapolis-Saint%20Paul%2C%20saw%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20jumps%20in%20poverty%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20Brookings%20found.%20No%20suburban%20community%20in%20a%20major%20metro%20area%20saw%20its%20poor%20population%20decline%20between%202019%20and%202022%2C%20but%20some%20saw%20an%20influx%20in%20new%20residents%20living%20above%20the%20poverty%20line%2C%20which%20brought%20their%20poverty%20rates%20down.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20suburbs%20still%20count%20among%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2019-03-07%2Fthe-decline-of-the-suburbs-is-at-odds-with-the-data%5C%22%3Ethe%20wealthiest%20communities%20in%20the%20country%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20the%20rate%20of%20poverty%20is%20rising%20faster%20in%20suburbs%20than%20in%20cities%20overall%2C%20cities%20still%20have%20a%20higher%20per%20capita%20poverty%20rate%20on%20average.%20In%202022%2C%209.6%25%20of%20suburban%20dwellers%20lived%20in%20poverty%2C%20while%2016.2%25%20of%20residents%20of%20major%20cities%20were%20poor%2C%20Brookings%20noted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20in%20the%20geography%20of%20poverty%20in%20the%20US%20is%20a%20result%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fthe-changing-geography-of-us-poverty%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20variety%20of%20factors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20rising%20housing%20costs%20in%20urban%20areas.%20More%20upwardly%20mobile%20and%20affluent%20people%20have%20moved%20into%20cities%20over%20the%20last%20two%20decades%2C%20helping%20bid%20up%20rents%20and%20home%20prices%2C%20which%20has%20fueled%20an%20affordability%20crisis%20in%20cities%20across%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20housing%20costs%20have%20shot%20up%20even%20more%2C%20pushing%20many%20lower-income%20people%20out%20into%20the%20suburbs.%20Suburban%20communities%20have%20also%20grown%20and%20attracted%20a%20more%20diverse%20population%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20and%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20including%20low-wage%20employment%20%E2%80%94%20have%20increasingly%20moved%20outside%20urban%20cores.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20in%20suburban%20poverty%20poses%20a%20challenge%20for%20many%20suburban%20areas%20that%20don't%20have%20particularly%20robust%20mass%20transit%20systems%2C%20lack%20a%20strong%20network%20of%20non-profit%20groups%20assisting%20low-income%20folks%2C%20and%20don't%20have%20well-funded%20social%20services.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuburban-areas-poverty-rising-faster-than-cities-post-pandemic-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697709721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652fe739be9edfa8eda39544%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuburban-areas-poverty-rising-faster-than-cities-post-pandemic-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Suburbs%20in%20major%20metros%20areas%20in%20the%20South%2C%20West%2C%20and%20Midwest%20saw%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20jumps%20in%20poverty%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuburban-areas-poverty-rising-faster-than-cities-post-pandemic-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20marketing%20failure%20that's%20going%20to%20kill%20us%20all%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amid%20the%20rising%20tide%20of%20the%20ocean's%20waves%20are%20floating%20ephemera%20of%20environmental%20marketing%3A%20A%20large%20orange%20billboard%20that%20says%20%26quot%3BSave%20The%20Earth%26quot%3B%20in%20bright%20yellow%20letters%20with%20a%20picture%20of%20the%20Earth%20underneath%2C%20flyers%20that%20say%20%26quot%3BSave%20The%20Whales%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3BClimate%20Action%20Now%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20%26quot%3BFight%20for%20Clean%20Energy%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20a%20petition.%20In%20the%20background%20a%20mostly%20submerged%20Statue%20of%20Liberty%20pokes%20out%20from%20the%20ocean's%20blue%20waves.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652da40355f52b01b360ce69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECampaigns%20to%20help%20the%20environment%20aren't%20working.%20We%20need%20better%20messaging.%3Cp%3EArantza%20Pena%20Popo%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESave%20the%20whales.%20Stop%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-to-issue-executive-order-against-keystone-pipeline-permit-report-says-2021-1%5C%22%3EKeystone%20XL%20pipeline%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Ban%20Arctic%20drilling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESlogans%20like%20these%20have%20been%20plastered%20on%20bumper%20stickers%20and%20chanted%20at%20marches%20for%20years.%20But%20despite%20being%20succinct%20earworms%2C%20they've%20all%20failed%20to%20address%20one%20key%20question%3A%20Why%3F%20Why%20should%20the%20typical%20American%20%E2%80%94%20worried%20about%20holding%20on%20to%20their%20job%2C%20providing%20for%20their%20family%2C%20and%20a%20million%20mundane%20challenges%20%E2%80%94%20get%20invested%20in%20protecting%20the%20environment%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20prevent%20a%20climate%20catastrophe%2C%20activists%20say.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20it's%20our%20moral%20responsibility%20as%20stewards%20of%20the%20planet%2C%20environmentalists%20argue.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20those%20reasons%20typically%20fall%20flat%20with%20the%20general%20public.%20Too%20often%2C%20issues%20that%20are%20critical%20to%20maintaining%20life%20on%20this%20planet%2C%20such%20as%20saving%20endangered%20species%20from%20extinction%20and%20blocking%20fossil-fuel%20development%2C%20get%20framed%20solely%20as%20ethical%20matters.%20Or%20worse%2C%20they%20get%20lost%20in%20a%20haze%20of%20confusing%20scientific%20jargon%20or%20grandiose%20calls%20to%20action.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20decades%20of%20scientific%20reports%20and%20widespread%20activism%2C%20nearly%20half%20of%20Americans%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F08%2F09%2Fwhat-the-data-says-about-americans-views-of-climate-change%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%20poll%20said%20they%20didn't%20view%20climate%20change%20as%20a%20major%20threat.%20And%2056%25%20said%20they%20thought%20that%20they%2C%20as%20individuals%2C%20were%20already%20doing%20enough%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20too%20much%20%E2%80%94%20to%20reduce%20the%20effects%20of%20climate%20change.%20It's%20that%20profound%20disconnect%20between%20perception%20and%20reality%20that's%20preventing%20us%20from%20taking%20the%20kind%20of%20urgent%20and%20sustained%20action%20necessary%20to%20prevent%20a%20planetwide%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-change-effects-adapt-or-die-un-ipcc-report-2022-3%5C%22%3Ecatastrophe%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20isn't%20that%20there's%20a%20lack%20of%20scientific%20information%20or%20moral%20reasons%20to%20act.%20The%20problem%20comes%20down%20to%20ineffective%20marketing.%20To%20connect%20with%20the%20average%20person%2C%20environmental%20campaigns%20need%20to%20focus%20more%20on%20how%20helping%20the%20environment%20helps%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarketing%2C%20at%20its%20core%2C%20is%20about%20shaping%20perception.%20And%20while%20the%20complexity%20and%20scale%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%20can%20be%20difficult%20to%20capture%20in%20a%20tagline%2C%20we%20need%20to%20draw%20on%20the%20profession's%20proven%20expertise%20at%20persuasion%20to%20help%20raise%20awareness%2C%20mobilize%20the%20public%2C%20and%20shift%20our%20national%20priorities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20enough%2C%20marketing%20experts%20say%2C%20to%20emphasize%20that%20an%20issue%20is%20important.%20%26quot%3BEven%20great%20and%20important%20things%20don't%20often%20get%20the%20attention%20they%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20Jonah%20Berger%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20marketing%20at%20the%20Wharton%20School%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20lots%20of%20things%20competing%20for%20people's%20attention.%20That's%20why%20we%20need%20to%20think%20about%20messaging.%26quot%3B%20Translating%20the%20climate%20crisis%20into%20an%20effective%20marketing%20campaign%2C%20he%20said%2C%20means%20focusing%20not%20on%20the%20abstract%20importance%20of%20the%20issue%20but%20on%20the%20concrete%20needs%20of%20the%20audience.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EClimate%20issues%20are%20often%20framed%20as%20a%20choice%20between%20selfishness%20and%20selflessness%3A%20Either%20you%20care%20about%20your%20money%20and%20your%20job%2C%20or%20you%20care%20about%20helping%20the%20planet.%20In%20this%20false%20dichotomy%2C%20it's%20clear%20where%20most%20people%20come%20down%3A%20In%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F1675%2Fmost-important-problem.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Americans%2C%20only%203%25%20of%20respondents%20ranked%20the%20environment%20as%20the%20most%20important%20issue%20facing%20the%20country%20today%2C%20versus%2034%25%20who%20said%20the%20economy%20was%20most%20important.%20Average%20people%2C%20this%20seems%20to%20suggest%2C%20are%20more%20concerned%20about%20whether%20they%20will%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20a%20good%20life%20for%20their%20children%20than%20whether%20certain%20animals%20will%20be%20around%20in%2030%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reality%2C%20though%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-the-climate-crisis-can-change-make-economy-better-resilient-2023-9%5C%22%3Ethe%20economy%20and%20environment%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20intricately%20intertwined.%20Increasing%20the%20energy%20efficiency%20of%20your%20home%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20a%20clear%20way%20to%20reduce%20your%20utility%20bills.%20But%20that's%20not%20how%20environmental%20issues%20are%20usually%20marketed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsider%20the%20Keystone%20XL%20pipeline%2C%20which%20was%20designed%20to%20bring%20oil%20sands%20from%20Canada%20into%20the%20US.%20The%20political%20left%20opposed%20the%20pipeline%20on%20environmental%20grounds%2C%20including%20its%20perpetuation%20of%20fossil-fuel%20reliance%20and%20the%20potential%20for%20oil%20spills.%20The%20right%20supported%20the%20pipeline%20on%20economic%20grounds%2C%20claiming%20that%20its%20construction%20would%20generate%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fstory%2F2012%2F01%2Fpoll-public-says-keystone-xl-a-jobs-win-072199%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%20100%2C000%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Keystone%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F54dc04cbeab8eab41f761a27%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22533%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20battle%20over%20the%20Keystone%20XL%20pipeline%20should%20never%20have%20been%20framed%20as%20the%20environment%20vs.%20the%20economy.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FJonathan%20Ernst%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20battle%20over%20the%20pipeline%20should%20never%20have%20been%20framed%20as%20a%20choice%20between%20the%20environment%20and%20the%20economy.%20Better%20marketing%20would%20have%20emphasized%20the%20very%20real%20and%20immediate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-climate-change-crisis-extreme-weather-is-costing-you-2023-9%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20climate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20the%20pipeline%20may%20have%20exacerbated%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20all%20the%20jobs%20that%20could%20be%20created%20by%20focusing%20on%20clean%20energy%2C%20not%20just%20fossil%20fuels.%20(That's%20the%20message%20the%20Biden%20administration%20adopted%20to%20promote%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%2C%20touting%20the%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2023%2F08%2F16%2Ffact-sheet-one-year-in-president-bidens-inflation-reduction-act-is-driving-historic-climate-action-and-investing-in-america-to-create-good-paying-jobs-and-reduce-costs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E170%2C000%20estimated%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20created%20in%20one%20year.)%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnvironmental%20advocates%20still%20struggle%20to%20make%20seemingly%20far-off%20issues%20a%20kitchen-table%20concern%20for%20Americans.%20Take%20oil%20drilling%20in%20Alaska%2C%20for%20example.%20When%20campaigns%20to%20ban%20Arctic%20drilling%20focus%20on%20protecting%20local%20ecosystems%2C%20that%20can%20leave%20people%20who%20live%20far%20from%20the%20Arctic%20wondering%20why%20the%20issue%20matters%20to%20them.%20Fortunately%2C%20that%20messaging%20is%20starting%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20approved%20the%20Willow%20project%20for%20oil%20drilling%20in%20the%20National%20Petroleum%20Reserve-Alaska%2C%20which%20drew%20significant%20backlash%20from%20environmental%20advocates.%20Attempts%20to%20reframe%20the%20discussion%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20global%20effects%20of%20the%20drilling%2C%20such%20as%20more%20extreme%20weather%2C%20have%20had%20more%20success%2C%20Jenna%20DiPaolo%2C%20the%20chief%20communications%20officer%20of%20Greenpeace%20USA%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20there%20were%20images%20of%20the%20pristine%20wilderness%2C%20there%20was%20also%20a%20lot%20of%20messaging%20about%20the%20impact%20this%20project%20would%20have%20on%20our%20global%20climate%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20consequently%2C%20on%20our%20ability%20to%20breathe%20clean%20air%2C%20drink%20clean%20water%2C%20and%20not%20suffer%20ever-worsening%20hurricanes%2C%20floods%2C%20and%20fires%2C%26quot%3B%20DiPaolo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20human-centric%20messaging%20had%20a%20somewhat%20positive%20impact.%20In%20September%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F09%2F06%2Fclimate%2Fbiden-drilling-alaska-wildlife-refuge.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20expanded%20environmental%20protections%20in%20the%20petroleum%20reserve%20and%20canceled%3C%2Fa%3E%20oil-%20and%20gas-lease%20sales%20in%20the%20nearby%20Arctic%20National%20Wildlife%20Refuge.%20Still%2C%20a%20new%20administration%20could%20easily%20switch%20back%20to%20more%20fossil-fuel-friendly%20policies.%20And%20while%20some%20environmental%20groups%20try%20to%20bring%20the%20issues%20home%2C%20too%20much%20marketing%20still%20focuses%20on%20morality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20many%20companies%20have%20tried%20to%20market%20their%20products%20by%20presenting%20them%20as%20climate-friendly.%20But%20those%20campaigns%20have%20produced%20some%20notable%20missteps.%20A%20good%20example%20of%20bad%20climate%20marketing%20comes%20from%20the%20Irish%20budget%20airline%20Ryanair.%20Since%20air%20travel%20blasts%20a%20lot%20of%20carbon%20emissions%20into%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20hastening%20the%20effects%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20airlines%20such%20as%20Ryanair%20have%20started%20offering%20flyers%20ways%20to%20%26quot%3Boffset%26quot%3B%20the%20emissions%20caused%20by%20their%20travel.%20Carbon%20offsets%20involve%20contributing%20money%20to%20a%20project%20that%20will%20help%20avoid%2C%20reduce%2C%20or%20remove%20carbon%20emissions%20from%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20such%20as%20planting%20trees%20or%20building%20wind%20farms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20Ryanair%20started%20offering%20customers%20the%20option%20to%20pay%20an%20additional%20fee%20to%20offset%20the%20carbon%20footprint%20of%20their%20flights.%20One%20offsetting%20project%20the%20airline%20chose%20tracked%20whales%20in%20Ireland%20to%20help%20preserve%20the%20species.%20The%20selection%20left%20many%20people%20feeling%20confused.%20What%20does%20saving%20the%20whales%20have%20to%20do%20with%20offsetting%20carbon%20emissions%20from%20jet%20fuel%3F%20The%20comedian%20John%20Oliver%20even%20mocked%20Ryanair%20during%20a%202022%20segment%20of%20his%20show%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D6p8zAbFKpW0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELast%20Week%20Tonight%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20for%20putting%20carbon-offset%20funds%20toward%20the%20whale%20project.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20that%20people%20would%20object%20to%20that.%20Of%20course%2C%20people%20love%20whales%20and%20dolphins%2C%26quot%3B%20Oliver%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20protecting%20them%20isn't%20the%20thing%20that%20you%20promised.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EWe%20are%20intrinsically%20selfish%20beings.%20We%20want%20to%20know%20what%20it%20means%20for%20us.%3C%2Fq%3E%20%3Ccite%3EBen%20Forman%2C%20CEO%20of%20Wrestler%3C%2Fcite%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20whale%20preservation%20does%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20have%20a%20lot%20to%20do%20with%20combating%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20Whales%20fertilize%20oceans%2C%20creating%20conditions%20for%20the%20growth%20of%20microscopic%20algae%2C%20which%20can%20capture%20carbon.%20And%20when%20whales%20die%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarinesanctuary.org%2Fblog%2Fwhale-fall-101%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20fall%20to%20the%20ocean%20floor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20carrying%20carbon%20in%20their%20bodies%20that%20will%20stay%20out%20of%20the%20atmosphere%20for%20hundreds%20of%20years.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20saving%20the%20planet%2C%20one%20whale%20is%20worth%20thousands%20of%20trees%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imf.org%2Fen%2FPublications%2Ffandd%2Fissues%2F2019%2F12%2Fnatures-solution-to-climate-change-chami%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20the%20bigger%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrypto-climate-scheme-carbon-credits-offsets-market-flowcarbon-2022-7%5C%22%3Eproblems%20with%20carbon%20offsets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20key%20mistake%20Ryanair%20made%20was%20that%20it%20didn't%20explain%3Cem%3E%20why%3C%2Fem%3E%20saving%20the%20whales%20was%20critical%20to%20reducing%20carbon%20emissions%2C%20which%20ultimately%20helps%20people%20enjoy%20life%20on%20this%20planet.%20Companies%20trying%20to%20present%20themselves%20as%20climate-friendly%20typically%20fail%20to%20make%20that%20link%2C%20leading%20people%20to%20dismiss%20their%20environmental%20efforts%20as%20corporate%20eyewash.%20Considering%20that%20only%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.ryanair.com%2Fsustainability%2Fcustomer-carbon-offsetting%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3%25%20of%20Ryanair%20passengers%20participate%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20carbon-offsetting%20program%2C%20the%20airline's%20marketing%20efforts%20clearly%20did%20not%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20most%20successful%20corporate%20efforts%20at%20climate%20marketing%20place%20more%20emphasis%20on%20consumers'%20personal%20concerns.%20Ben%20Forman%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20marketing%20agency%20Wrestler%2C%20has%20worked%20on%20campaigns%20for%20the%20sustainable-shoe%20company%20Allbirds.%20While%20being%20good%20for%20the%20environment%20is%20a%20key%20part%20of%20the%20brand%2C%20that's%20not%20the%20sole%20focus%20of%20how%20Allbirds%20markets%20the%20shoes.%20For%20example%3Cstrong%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EForman%20said%2C%20the%20company%20emphasizes%20how%20its%20use%20of%20sustainable%20materials%2C%20such%20as%20merino%20wool%2C%20improves%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20shoe.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EBusinesses%20can%20get%20lost%20talking%20about%20sustainability%20by%20putting%20it%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20their%20messaging%2C%20when%20instead%20the%20focus%20should%20be%20on%20the%20product%20first%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20intrinsically%20selfish%20beings%2C%26quot%3B%20Forman%20added.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20know%20what%20it%20means%20for%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20is%20another%20example%20of%20a%20popular%20brand%20that's%20sustainability-adjacent%20and%20has%20successfully%20marketed%20itself%20without%20getting%20bogged%20down%20in%20the%20environmental%20details.%20%26quot%3BThey've%20done%20a%20really%20neat%20job%20of%20realizing%20that%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20that%20people%20buy%20a%20car%20is%20not%20just%20because%20they%20care%20about%20the%20environment%20but%20because%20they%20care%20about%20looking%20good%20to%20their%20peers%2C%26quot%3B%20Berger%2C%20the%20marketing%20professor%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20enough%20organizations%20are%20taking%20this%20approach%20and%20moving%20the%20needle%20toward%20a%20more%20sustainable%20world.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Freports%2Fco2-emissions-in-2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInternational%20Energy%20Agency%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20global%20carbon%20emissions%20reached%20a%20record%20high%20last%20year.%20It's%20clear%20that%20the%20current%20marketing%20approach%20to%20the%20climate%20crisis%20isn't%20cutting%20it.%20Sounding%20the%20alarm%20bells%20isn't%20enough.%20People%20need%20to%20see%20what's%20in%20it%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20talking%20about%20emissions%20levels%2C%20talk%20about%20how%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fnewsreleases%2Fepa-releases-report-showing-health-impacts-climate-change-children-united-states%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclimate%20crisis%20could%20increase%3C%2Fa%3E%20childhood%20asthma%20rates%20and%20incidences%20of%20Lyme%20disease.%20Instead%20of%20talking%20about%20why%20sharks%20are%20awe-inspiring%20creatures%2C%20talk%20about%20how%20keeping%20them%20alive%20provides%20more%20%3Ca%20rel%3