Asian%2C%20Arab%20and%20Latin%20American%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENuanced%20writing%20on%20genocidal%20histories%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUlrich%20Noller%2C%20a%20journalist%2C%20left%20the%20LiBeraturpreis%20jury%20in%20protest%20at%20the%20award%2C%20denouncing%20Shibli%E2%80%99s%20book%20as%20portraying%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20State%20of%20Israel%20as%20a%20murder%20machine%E2%80%9D.%20And%20a%20review%20in%20the%20widely%20read%2C%20left-leaning%20German%20newspaper%2C%20Die%20Tageszeitung%20(The%20Daily%20Newspaper)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Foct%2F15%2Fpalestinian-voices-shut-down-at-frankfurt-book-fair-say-authors%5C%22%3Ealleged%20that%20the%20novel%20used%3C%2Fa%3E%20anti-Israel%20and%20anti-Semitic%20narratives%2C%20adding%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20short%20novel%2C%20all%20Israelis%20are%20rapists%20and%20murderers%2C%20while%20the%20Palestinians%20are%20victims%20of%20trigger-happy%20occupiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20perspectives%20were%20not%20shared%20by%20other%20members%20of%20the%20Litprom%20jury%2C%20nor%20by%20many%20other%20critics.%20The%20book%20has%20been%20nominated%20in%20the%20US%20for%20the%20National%20Book%20Awards%20and%20the%20International%20Book%20Awards.%20Its%20admirers%20include%20J.M.%20Coetzee%20and%20Australian%20writer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FMireilleJuchau%2Fstatus%2F1713689208400089362%5C%22%3EMireille%20Juchau%2C%20who%20wrote%20this%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20ever%20we%20need%20nuanced%20writing%20on%20the%20irrefutable%20ways%20violent%20and%20genocidal%20histories%20exert%20their%20power%20on%20the%20present.%20Adania%20Shibli%E2%80%99s%20Minor%20Detail%20is%20one%20of%20the%20finest%20recent%20examples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3ENeither%20Litprom%20nor%20the%20director%20of%20the%20book%20fair%2C%20Juergen%20Boos%2C%20invoked%20anti-Semitism%20as%20a%20reason%20for%20cancelling%20the%20award%20ceremony.%20In%20fact%2C%20they%20said%20the%20ceremony%20would%20go%20ahead%20at%20a%20future%20time%20and%20place%2C%20yet%20to%20be%20fixed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.litprom.de%2Fbests-bucher%2Fliberaturpreis%2Fpreistragerin-2023%2F%5C%22%3ELitprom%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20the%20war%20started%20by%20Hamas%2C%20under%20which%20millions%20of%20people%20in%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%20are%20suffering%2C%20the%20organizer%20Litprom%20decided%20not%20to%20hold%20the%20award%20ceremony%20of%20the%20LiBeraturpreis%20at%20the%20Frankfurt%20Book%20Fair.%20Litprom%20is%20looking%20for%20a%20suitable%20format%20and%20setting%20for%20the%20event%20at%20a%20later%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoos%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.buchmesse.de%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fisrael%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DIsrael%2520Statement%2520EN-%2C%2522We%2520want%2520to%2520make%2520Jewish%2520and%2520Israeli%2520voices%2520especially%2520visible%2CBoos%252C%2520Director%2520of%2520Frankfurter%2520Buchmesse%5C%22%3Ein%20his%20statement%20announcing%20the%20cancellation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20strongly%20condemn%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20barbaric%20terror%20war%20against%20Israel%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20Frankfurter%20Buchmesse%20has%20always%20been%20about%20humanity%2C%20its%20focus%20has%20always%20been%20on%20peaceful%20and%20democratic%20discourse%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20Frankfurter%20Buchmesse%20stands%20with%20complete%20solidarity%20on%20the%20side%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20Israeli%20and%20Jewish%20voices%20would%20be%20given%20additional%20time%20on%20the%20book%20fair%E2%80%99s%20stages%20and%20that%20an%20event%20called%20%E2%80%9COut%20of%20Concern%20for%20Israel%E2%80%9D%20would%20be%20staged%20in%20the%20fair%E2%80%99s%20cultural%20and%20political%20pavilion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETreated%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98symbol%E2%80%99%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20consistent%20with%20the%20widespread%20reaction%20to%20the%20atrocities%20committed%20by%20Hamas%20in%20southern%20Israel.%20They%20are%20on%20a%20scale%20of%20savagery%20seldom%20brought%20into%20public%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYet%20it%20is%20not%20alleged%20that%20Shibli%20has%20any%20sympathy%20for%20Hamas%20or%20its%20atrocities.%20And%20it%20is%20clear%20from%20the%20statements%20of%20both%20Litprom%20and%20Boos%20that%20their%20reasons%20for%20cancelling%20the%20award%20ceremony%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20either%20the%20merits%20of%20Shibli%E2%80%99s%20novel%20or%20her%20conduct%20as%20a%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20question%20arises%3A%20what%20is%20the%20connection%20between%20Shibli%20and%20the%20Hamas%20atrocities%3F%20This%20is%20the%20ground%20on%20which%20the%20ceremony%20is%20being%20cancelled.%20When%20asked%20to%20clarify%20the%20connection%20they%20perceived%20between%20Shibli%20and%20Hamas%2C%20Litprom%20told%20The%20Conversation%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAgainst%20the%20background%20of%20the%20polarized%20situation%20in%20Germany%2C%20in%20which%20parts%20of%20the%20media%20tried%20to%20scandalize%20the%20celebration%20of%20the%20award%2C%20we%20thought%20it%20right%20to%20hold%20the%20award%20ceremony%20at%20a%20different%20time%20in%20a%20less%20politically%20charged%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3ELitprom%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftaz.de%2FDebatte-um-Autorin-Adania-Shibli%2F!5965811%2F%5C%22%3Ecited%20the%20Die%20Tageszeitung%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20read%20in%20part%3A%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20the%20mass%20murders%20of%20the%20Hamas%20terrorists%2C%20the%20awarding%20of%20the%20prize%20would%20be%20almost%20unbearable.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIs%20Shibli%20being%20treated%20as%20a%20symbol%20because%20she%20is%20Palestinian%2C%20and%20her%20book%20is%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20a%20Palestinian%3F%20If%20so%2C%20that%20would%20put%20her%20ethnicity%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20decision-making%2C%20which%20would%20be%20an%20appalling%20injustice%20to%20her%20as%20an%20individual%20and%20a%20violation%20of%20principles%20stated%20in%20Article%202%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fabout-us%2Funiversal-declaration-of-human-rights%5C%22%3EUniversal%20Declaration%20of%20Human%20Rights%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAgainst%20free%20speech%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20objection%20to%20the%20Frankfurt%20decision%20is%20that%20it%20is%20an%20unjustified%20and%20counterproductive%20abridgement%20of%20free%20speech.%20This%20argument%20has%20been%20taken%20up%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fentertainment-arts%2Fbooks%2Fstory%2F2023-10-16%2Fadania-shinli-book-prize-cancellation%5C%22%3Emore%20than%201%2C000%20literary%20figures%3C%2Fa%3E%20globally%2C%20including%20Irish%20novelist%20Colm%20T%C3%B3ib%C3%ADn%2C%20Pulitzer%20Prize-winning%20author%20Hisham%20Matar%2C%20Man%20Booker%20Prize%20finalist%20Rachel%20Kushner%20and%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Prize%20winner%20Kamila%20Shamsie.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20open%20letter%20to%20the%20Frankfurt%20Book%20Fair%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Foct%2F15%2Fpalestinian-voices-shut-down-at-frankfurt-book-fair-say-authors%5C%22%3Ethey%20make%20the%20important%20point%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20this%20is%20the%20very%20time%20Palestinian%20writers%20should%20be%20given%20space%20to%20share%20their%20thoughts%2C%20feelings%20and%20reflections.%20Doing%20so%20would%20seem%20to%20be%20consistent%20with%20Jurgen%20Boos%E2%80%99%20assertion%20that%20the%20book%20fair%20has%20always%20been%20focused%20on%20peaceful%20and%20democratic%20discourse.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20dialogue%20has%20any%20part%20in%20peaceful%20and%20democratic%20discourse%2C%20shutting%20down%20Palestinian%20literary%20voices%20at%20this%20time%20seems%20to%20work%20against%20this%20objective.%20The%20protesting%20authors%20go%20further%20and%20call%20it%20irresponsible.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20seems%20to%20be%20no%20reason%20why%20the%20book%20fair%20should%20not%20give%20Israeli%20and%20Jewish%20voices%20the%20additional%20time%20and%20visibility%20that%20is%20undoubtedly%20justified%2C%20while%20continuing%20with%20the%20LiBeraturpreis%20award%20ceremony.%20Doing%20so%20would%20be%20a%20powerful%20symbol%20of%20its%20own%2C%20a%20demonstration%20that%20the%20book%20fair%20is%20indeed%20a%20place%20for%20peaceful%20and%20democratic%20discourse.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOf%20course%20there%20are%20always%20security%20considerations%20to%20be%20taken%20into%20account%2C%20especially%20at%20a%20time%20of%20such%20heightened%20emotions.%20But%20these%2C%20too%2C%20have%20not%20been%20invoked%20by%20the%20organisers%20as%20a%20reason%20for%20the%20cancellation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20this%20cancellation%20was%20an%20ethically%20indefensible%20decision%20%E2%80%93%20sending%20exactly%20the%20wrong%20signals%20at%20exactly%20the%20wrong%20time.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F215712%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fdenis-muller-1865%5C%22%3EDenis%20Muller%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Senior%20Research%20Fellow%2C%20Centre%20for%20Advancing%20Journalism%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Fthe-university-of-melbourne-722%5C%22%3EThe%20University%20of%20Melbourne%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20