0Gaza%E2%80%99s%20south%2C%20although%20evacuation%20routes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fpalestinians-fleeing-fighting-south-find-no-escape-danger-2023-10-15%2F%5C%22%3Ehave%20also%20been%20bombed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20century%20of%20underfunding%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20devastation%20to%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20health%20system%20is%20obvious.%20But%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20health%20care%20system%20was%20already%20under%20stress%20before%20the%20latest%20bombardment.%20In%20fact%2C%20policies%20that%20stretch%20back%20decades%20have%20left%20it%20unable%20to%20meet%20even%20the%20basic%20health%20needs%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20residents%2C%20let%20alone%20respond%20to%20the%20ongoing%20humanitarian%20catastrophe.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FKy3de%2F6%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Where%20is%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%3F%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22593%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Funispal%2Fhistory%2F%5C%22%3Ejust%20over%20a%20century%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20health%20system%20in%20Gaza%20has%20been%20administered%20by%20six%20authorities%3A%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jewishvirtuallibrary.org%2Fottoman-rule-1517-1917%5C%22%3EOttomans%20until%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20I%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3445003%2Fmandatory-palestine%2F%5C%22%3EBritish%20during%20the%20mandate%20period%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%201917%20to%201947%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fembassies.gov.il%2FMFA%2FAboutIsrael%2FMaps%2FPages%2F1949-1967%2520Armistice%2520Lines.aspx%5C%22%3EEgypt%20from%201949%20to%201967%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Israel%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Ffeatures%2F2018%2F6%2F4%2Fthe-naksa-how-israel-occupied-the-whole-of-palestine-in-1967%5C%22%3Eoccupation%20starting%20in%201967%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20then%20a%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20led%20first%20by%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20from%201995-2006%20and%20since%20then%20by%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20each%20have%20had%20in%20common%20is%20that%2C%20from%20my%20perspective%20as%20a%20global%20health%20expert%2C%20they%20invested%20little%20in%20Palestinian%20health.%20For%20periods%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20the%20health%20priorities%20of%20successive%20governing%20bodies%20appeared%20focused%20more%20on%20reducing%20the%20spread%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC1847484%2F%5C%22%3Ecommunicable%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20protect%20foreigners%20interacting%20with%20the%20native%20Palestinian%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20seemingly%20far%20less%20attention%20paid%20to%20building%20health%20infrastructure%2C%20adequately%20training%20health%20personnel%2C%20promoting%20preventive%20care%20and%20other%20long-term%20initiatives%20that%20make%20up%20a%20sustainable%20health%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20Israeli%20occupation%20from%201967%2C%20several%20Palestinian%20hospitals%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Funispal%2Fdocument%2Fauto-insert-201580%2F%5C%22%3Eturned%20into%20detention%20centers%20or%20military%20offices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20others%20were%20closed%2C%20and%20new%20ones%20were%20prohibited%20from%20opening.%20Palestinian%20physicians%20working%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories%20earned%20one-third%20the%20salary%20of%20their%20Israeli%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20this%20neglect%2C%20health%20indicators%20throughout%20what%20are%20now%20called%20the%20occupied%20territories%20%E2%80%93%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%20Strip%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20poor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMaternal%20and%20infant%20mortality%20%E2%80%93%20typical%20indicators%20of%20health%20system%20functioning%20%E2%80%93%20tends%20to%20be%20high.%20For%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Funispal%2Fdocument%2Fauto-insert-201580%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20mid-1980s%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20infant%20mortality%20was%20over%2030%20per%201%2C000%20live%20births%20for%20Palestinians%2C%20compared%20with%20just%20under%2010%20per%201%2C000%20among%20the%20Jewish%20population%20of%20Israel.%20And%20infant%20mortality%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2Finfant-mortality-gaza-no-longer-decline-%25E2%2580%259Calarming-trend%25E2%2580%259D-according-new%5C%22%3Eremained%20stubbornly%20high%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20a%20lack%20of%20a%20reliable%20drinkable%20water%20infrastructure%20and%20overall%20unsanitary%20conditions%20resulted%20in%20the%20spread%20of%20parasitic%20and%20other%20infectious%20diseases%2C%20like%20rotavirus%2C%20cholera%20and%20salmonella%20%E2%80%93%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.com%2Fmiddle-east-news%2Fpalestinians%2F2018-10-16%2Fty-article-magazine%2F.premium%2Fpolluted-water-a-leading-cause-of-gazan-child-mortality-says-rand-corp-study%2F0000017f-e847-dc7e-adff-f8ef68c50000%5C%22%3Eremain%20leading%20causes%20of%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDying%20before%20they%20can%20leave%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMost%20residents%20of%20Gaza%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prb.org%2Fresources%2Fthe-west-bank-and-gaza-a-population-profile%2F%5C%22%3Efled%20there%20in%201948%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20being%20displaced%20from%20their%20homes%20in%20what%20became%20the%20state%20of%20Israel.%20They%20were%20classified%20as%20refugees%2C%20many%20receiving%20limited%20services%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fabout_unrwa.pdf%5C%22%3EUnited%20Nations%20Relief%20and%20Works%20Agency%20for%20Palestine%20Refugees%20in%20the%20Near%20East%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20was%20established%20in%201949.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20chronic%20underfunding%20of%20public%20hospitals%20has%20meant%20that%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20have%20remained%20reliant%20on%20outside%20money%20and%20nongovernmental%20organizations%20for%20essential%20health%20services.%20This%20started%20a%20trend%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freliefweb.int%2Freport%2Fworld%2Fdependency-and-humanitarian-relief-critical-analysis%5C%22%3Ehumanitarian%20dependence%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20continues%20to%20this%20day%2C%20with%20many%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20health%20facilities%20funded%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20humanitarian%20agencies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.msf.org%2Fhospitals-are-overwhelmed-catastrophic-situation-gaza%5C%22%3EDoctors%20Without%20Borders%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20religious%20organizations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhistory.state.gov%2Fmilestones%2F1993-2000%2Foslo%5C%22%3EOslo%20Accords%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20mid-1990s%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20was%20established%20to%20administer%20services%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories.%20The%20accords%20called%20for%20health%20responsibilities%20to%20be%20transferred%20to%20the%20newly%20formed%20Palestinian%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20as%20preparation%20for%20a%20sovereign%20Palestinian%20state%2C%20which%20the%20accords%20called%20for%20within%20a%20five-year%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Palestinian%20Authority%20received%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farabcenterdc.org%2Fresource%2Finternational-aid-to-the-palestinians-between-politicization-and-development%2F%5C%22%3Esignificant%20influx%20of%20humanitarian%20aid%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20it%20took%20on%20civil%20responsibilities%2C%20including%20health.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20health%20indicators%20for%20Palestinians%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.worldbank.org%2Findicator%2FSP.DYN.LE00.IN%3Flocations%3DPS%5C%22%3Elife%20expectancy%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D