0Josh%20Paul%2C%20has%20resigned%20from%20his%20position%20because%20of%20the%20Joe%20Biden%20administrations%20response%20to%20the%20situation%20in%20Israel%20and%20Palestine.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fupdate%2Furn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7120512510645952512%2F%5C%22%3EPaul%20said%20on%20LinekdIn%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20his%20decision%20was%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Ca%20policy%20disagreement%20concerning%20our%20%5Bthe%20US%20government%E2%80%99s%5D%20continued%20lethal%20assistance%20to%20Israel%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20had%20my%20fair%20share%20of%20debates%20and%20discussions%20and%20efforts%20to%20shift%20policy%20on%20controversial%20arms%20sales%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fstate-department-resignation-gaza_n_65306079e4b00565b622b1fb%5C%22%3EPaul%20told%20%3Cem%3EHuffPost%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20his%20resignation.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20clear%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20arguing%20with%20this%20one.%20Given%20that%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20shift%20anything%2C%20I%20resigned.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPaul%20has%20worked%20in%20the%20State%20Department%E2%80%99s%20bureau%20of%20political-military%20affairs%20for%20more%20than%2011%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20note%20explaining%20his%20resignation%2C%20Paul%20referred%20to%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20surprise%20attack%20on%20Israel%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20monstrosity%20of%20monstrosities%E2%80%9D.%20However%2C%20he%20said%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20response%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20only%20lead%20to%20more%20and%20deeper%20suffering%20for%20both%20the%20Israeli%20and%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20%E2%80%93%20and%20is%20not%20in%20the%20long%20term%20American%20interest%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20Administration%E2%80%99s%20response%20%E2%80%93%20and%20much%20of%20Congress%E2%80%99%20as%20well%20%E2%80%93%20is%20an%20impulsive%20reaction%20built%20on%20confirmation%20bias%2C%20political%20convenienc